1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,310
[Disclaimer: This series is entirely fictional
and solely for entertainment purposes

2
00:00:04,340 --> 00:00:08,470
with no association or reference
to any individuals, places, or events;

3
00:00:08,500 --> 00:00:12,410
there may be inappropriate behaviors
and vulgarity based on the character's persona;

4
00:00:12,440 --> 00:00:14,780
viewer discretion is advised]

5
00:00:20,700 --> 00:00:21,840
I thought you were not going to come.

6
00:00:22,480 --> 00:00:23,460
What do you want?

7
00:00:23,480 --> 00:00:24,920
I just want to help you...

8
00:00:25,340 --> 00:00:28,040
maintain that fake happiness
for a long time.

9
00:00:28,360 --> 00:00:29,520
Tell me what you want.

10
00:00:30,840 --> 00:00:31,960
Five hundred thousand baht.

11
00:00:32,320 --> 00:00:33,440
Five hundred thousand?!

12
00:00:33,820 --> 00:00:36,600
I have no idea what you are asking me,

13
00:00:39,360 --> 00:00:41,360
but if it's time to say it,

14
00:00:42,200 --> 00:00:44,200
I'm going to tell you the truth.

15
00:00:47,520 --> 00:00:49,080
The entrance

16
00:00:49,120 --> 00:00:51,980
is decorated with stones to make customers

17
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:54,280
feel confident in our restaurant as they enter.

18
00:00:54,340 --> 00:00:57,040
The floor in the middle
is made of swirl-patterned wood,

19
00:00:57,200 --> 00:00:59,660
resembling the continuous flow
of water energy

20
00:00:59,680 --> 00:01:01,160
to attract many customers.

21
00:01:04,360 --> 00:01:06,260
You pay attention to
every detail, don't you?

22
00:01:06,720 --> 00:01:07,560
Exactly.

23
00:01:07,940 --> 00:01:11,320
Also, each private room
is differently decorated.

24
00:01:11,720 --> 00:01:13,440
Different, but still matching.

25
00:01:14,600 --> 00:01:17,120
But every room is already booked today.

26
00:01:17,140 --> 00:01:18,840
I'll give you the photos of them instead

27
00:01:19,880 --> 00:01:21,280
so that you can use them for your study.

28
00:01:22,600 --> 00:01:23,400
Thank you so much.

29
00:01:23,760 --> 00:01:24,760
This is what we call

30
00:01:25,360 --> 00:01:27,000
a masterful blend

31
00:01:27,440 --> 00:01:29,160
of superstition

32
00:01:29,360 --> 00:01:30,920
and design theory.

33
00:01:31,960 --> 00:01:32,880
A perfect balance.

34
00:01:34,820 --> 00:01:37,000
Let's have lunch together before you go.

35
00:01:37,880 --> 00:01:39,520
I want you to try our food here.

36
00:01:40,200 --> 00:01:43,560
I guarantee that the food
is as stunning as the decoration.

37
00:01:44,720 --> 00:01:46,920
Oh, unfortunately,

38
00:01:47,160 --> 00:01:49,920
I have a meeting
at the university after this.

39
00:01:50,640 --> 00:01:52,039
Maybe next time.

40
00:01:52,240 --> 00:01:54,160
Let's split up, okay?

41
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:56,400
- Goodbye.
- Goodbye.

42
00:02:00,690 --> 00:02:03,120
Excuse me, I'd like to use the toilet.

43
00:02:03,360 --> 00:02:05,360
It's over there.
Go straight and turn left.

44
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:06,720
Thank you.

45
00:02:18,920 --> 00:02:22,720
♫Is it pure coincidence?♫

46
00:02:22,970 --> 00:02:27,040
♫Or is it destiny that decides?♫

47
00:02:27,070 --> 00:02:29,370
♫Is someone above drawing all these lines?♫

48
00:02:29,400 --> 00:02:34,920
♫Or playing matchmaker in disguise?♫

49
00:02:35,540 --> 00:02:39,740
♫What if the stars shift in their place♫

50
00:02:39,930 --> 00:02:43,440
♫Slightly out of line,♫

51
00:02:44,170 --> 00:02:47,860
♫Will our orbits still align?♫

52
00:02:47,890 --> 00:02:52,200
♫Try answering if your world
will cross with mine♫

53
00:02:52,230 --> 00:02:56,280
♫Though the destiny between us
is differently defined♫

54
00:02:56,310 --> 00:03:01,560
♫And I believe our love has power♫

55
00:03:01,850 --> 00:03:05,700
♫I believe the love of us♫

56
00:03:05,730 --> 00:03:14,340
♫Will realign the stars back to the line
where they should be♫

57
00:03:14,360 --> 00:03:15,400
Let's go Dutch.

58
00:03:15,960 --> 00:03:18,680
You can transfer your share to my account.

59
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:23,160
You're still a treasurer
of our classroom as always.

60
00:03:23,560 --> 00:03:25,560
Yeah, has our classroom's leader

61
00:03:25,840 --> 00:03:28,920
changed the status from being single yet?

62
00:03:30,640 --> 00:03:32,820
I'm protective
of my single life, you know?

63
00:03:32,840 --> 00:03:34,060
Whoa.

64
00:03:34,079 --> 00:03:37,560
- Protective of your single life, huh?
- But Pitcha, a future famous artist,

65
00:03:37,720 --> 00:03:41,160
isn't allowed to be
someone's sweetheart, right?

66
00:03:44,180 --> 00:03:45,480
A secret of people in the industry

67
00:03:45,820 --> 00:03:47,540
can't be exposed, you know?

68
00:03:48,190 --> 00:03:48,960
So dramatic, huh?

69
00:03:50,030 --> 00:03:50,800
Wait.

70
00:03:51,280 --> 00:03:53,880
What if we dig up the old photos
of your sweetheart?

71
00:03:54,200 --> 00:03:55,880
Am I going to get a backlash?

72
00:03:57,079 --> 00:03:58,240
Why on earth would you do that?

73
00:03:58,440 --> 00:04:00,380
For social media engagement, you know?

74
00:04:00,400 --> 00:04:01,820
It's the point of having
a celebrity friend.

75
00:04:02,840 --> 00:04:04,280
Enough. Stop it.

76
00:04:04,520 --> 00:04:05,860
- Let's settle the bill.
- Let's transfer it.

77
00:04:05,880 --> 00:04:07,680
- I totally forgot.
- I almost forgot that.

78
00:04:14,060 --> 00:04:14,600
Let's go.

79
00:04:17,140 --> 00:04:18,040
Hey, guys.

80
00:04:18,140 --> 00:04:19,680
Who wants a ride back with me?

81
00:04:20,240 --> 00:04:21,079
Me. I'll go with you.

82
00:04:21,380 --> 00:04:23,040
You can drop me off at the train station.

83
00:04:29,640 --> 00:04:30,600
What about you, Pitcha?

84
00:04:31,920 --> 00:04:32,820
I'll take him home.

85
00:04:32,840 --> 00:04:33,680
Whoa.

86
00:04:33,800 --> 00:04:36,140
Doing a task for the old sweetheart

87
00:04:36,159 --> 00:04:37,440
as always, huh?

88
00:04:37,620 --> 00:04:39,480
Be careful. If his fans see this,

89
00:04:39,840 --> 00:04:41,120
this can become news.

90
00:04:41,220 --> 00:04:42,560
But if I wear these sunglasses,

91
00:04:43,680 --> 00:04:45,420
they'll have no idea who I am.

92
00:04:45,440 --> 00:04:46,940
- What are you doing?
- That's okay.

93
00:04:47,360 --> 00:04:48,720
You don't need to do this.

94
00:04:49,820 --> 00:04:51,620
Shall we have some selfies
together before we go?

95
00:04:51,640 --> 00:04:53,140
- Yeah, yeah.
- Come on.

96
00:05:10,880 --> 00:05:11,600
Pure,

97
00:05:12,500 --> 00:05:14,020
look at what I just sent you.

98
00:05:36,680 --> 00:05:38,820
Before we end, don't forget
to ask the tarot and me

99
00:05:38,840 --> 00:05:40,760
for forgiveness.

100
00:05:45,840 --> 00:05:48,000
The last prophecies were so accurate

101
00:05:48,030 --> 00:05:49,200
that they brought you here again, right?

102
00:05:49,720 --> 00:05:52,120
You just had a reading
not so long ago, though.

103
00:05:52,220 --> 00:05:53,280
Yeah, that's right.

104
00:05:53,500 --> 00:05:54,720
Now,

105
00:05:55,340 --> 00:05:56,680
many things

106
00:05:56,960 --> 00:05:58,560
are starting to come true.

107
00:05:59,080 --> 00:06:03,040
By the way, has Ritt,
the Prophecy Stone Master, quit reading?

108
00:06:03,280 --> 00:06:05,160
He has quit for a while.

109
00:06:05,220 --> 00:06:07,760
I'm his replacement.

110
00:06:07,920 --> 00:06:09,800
I can assure you that
I am just as accurate.

111
00:06:11,160 --> 00:06:12,040
Thank you so much.

112
00:06:27,180 --> 00:06:28,200
What are you doing here?

113
00:06:31,320 --> 00:06:32,480
I just...

114
00:06:33,330 --> 00:06:35,120
want to warn you

115
00:06:35,840 --> 00:06:37,800
that you're running out of time.

116
00:06:39,640 --> 00:06:40,880
Don't let me wait long.

117
00:06:42,440 --> 00:06:43,560
Otherwise...

118
00:06:50,580 --> 00:06:52,740
you probably know what will happen next.

119
00:07:03,480 --> 00:07:04,320
Ployplern,

120
00:07:04,600 --> 00:07:05,600
where is Pure?

121
00:07:06,080 --> 00:07:07,520
Maybe at the back.

122
00:07:08,220 --> 00:07:09,160
Hey, Ritt!

123
00:07:09,300 --> 00:07:10,860
Can you test a new deck for me?

124
00:07:10,880 --> 00:07:12,160
Just pick a card. That's all.

125
00:07:12,500 --> 00:07:13,700
Please, please.

126
00:07:13,720 --> 00:07:16,000
Let's test my accuracy,
Ployplern, the Pictura Master.

127
00:07:25,740 --> 00:07:28,820
If it comes out like this, it means...

128
00:07:29,560 --> 00:07:31,060
Check on all customers, okay?

129
00:07:31,090 --> 00:07:32,440
Don't let them wait.

130
00:07:38,159 --> 00:07:39,000
Hey...

131
00:07:39,520 --> 00:07:41,159
You forgot the stones at my bar again.

132
00:07:43,240 --> 00:07:44,880
You saw the photo I sent you, right?

133
00:07:47,380 --> 00:07:48,640
They finally met each other.

134
00:07:50,200 --> 00:07:53,040
I don't know when they met.

135
00:07:54,300 --> 00:07:55,680
What should I do, huh?

136
00:07:57,120 --> 00:07:59,040
But they looked completely fine.

137
00:08:00,540 --> 00:08:02,480
About this...

138
00:08:03,420 --> 00:08:04,400
I...

139
00:08:22,540 --> 00:08:23,920
You two should settle it yourselves.

140
00:08:41,380 --> 00:08:42,159
Pure

141
00:08:42,919 --> 00:08:44,120
sent me that photo.

142
00:08:50,880 --> 00:08:51,720
Today,

143
00:08:53,200 --> 00:08:54,800
you were also in that restaurant, right?

144
00:08:58,480 --> 00:08:59,180
Well...

145
00:09:00,400 --> 00:09:01,600
Pitcha and I...

146
00:09:01,620 --> 00:09:03,120
Did you know from the beginning

147
00:09:04,280 --> 00:09:06,280
that I wasn't your childhood sweetheart?

148
00:09:07,700 --> 00:09:09,640
You know I've lied to you.

149
00:09:10,880 --> 00:09:12,600
- Well...
- Was it really fun?

150
00:09:15,480 --> 00:09:16,680
And Pitcha

151
00:09:17,640 --> 00:09:18,840
also knew

152
00:09:19,720 --> 00:09:21,320
that I've been impersonating him, right?

153
00:09:29,520 --> 00:09:31,240
How could you guys do this?

154
00:09:32,400 --> 00:09:33,780
Do you think I'm some kind of clown?

155
00:09:35,200 --> 00:09:36,280
Have you been waiting

156
00:09:36,920 --> 00:09:38,920
to see how long I could lie to you?

157
00:09:39,920 --> 00:09:41,000
It's not like that.

158
00:09:41,950 --> 00:09:43,760
I thought

159
00:09:44,900 --> 00:09:46,500
I was so talented

160
00:09:47,700 --> 00:09:49,600
that I could make you believe me
without any doubt.

161
00:09:51,920 --> 00:09:52,920
But...

162
00:09:54,180 --> 00:09:56,080
the more talented one is actually you.

163
00:09:57,560 --> 00:09:59,560
You made me believe with all my heart

164
00:10:00,810 --> 00:10:03,040
that what happened between us was real,

165
00:10:03,900 --> 00:10:06,520
even though it was all our lies.

166
00:10:09,340 --> 00:10:10,200
Please let me explain first.

167
00:10:11,800 --> 00:10:12,840
What else do you want me to hear?!

168
00:10:13,620 --> 00:10:15,520
The next lie you're going to tell?!

169
00:10:16,600 --> 00:10:17,600
Be honest!

170
00:10:18,180 --> 00:10:19,080
What else should I know

171
00:10:19,110 --> 00:10:21,520
about your make-up stories?

172
00:10:32,800 --> 00:10:34,040
Liars like us,

173
00:10:35,040 --> 00:10:36,880
who love to make up stories,

174
00:10:37,600 --> 00:10:38,920
aren't supposed to be together.

175
00:10:40,720 --> 00:10:42,400
It's not going to work anyway.

176
00:11:26,680 --> 00:11:27,640
I'm sorry.

177
00:11:30,480 --> 00:11:31,840
Can you let me explain?

178
00:11:32,980 --> 00:11:34,320
I love you so much,

179
00:11:35,720 --> 00:11:37,480
but how could you do this to me?

180
00:11:38,720 --> 00:11:39,680
How?

181
00:11:39,700 --> 00:11:40,720
I'm so sorry.

182
00:11:43,280 --> 00:11:44,640
Let's go home and talk it out.

183
00:12:01,160 --> 00:12:02,520
Let's talk it out when we're home, okay?

184
00:12:04,560 --> 00:12:05,440
Please.

185
00:12:16,600 --> 00:12:17,440
Hey, Ritt.

186
00:12:18,060 --> 00:12:19,360
You came home pretty late, huh?

187
00:12:19,580 --> 00:12:20,620
Have you had anything yet?

188
00:12:25,980 --> 00:12:27,480
Excuse me, I'll go pack my things.

189
00:12:31,060 --> 00:12:32,160
Why pack?

190
00:12:42,200 --> 00:12:45,060
When we were young, it was the same.

191
00:12:45,080 --> 00:12:48,020
One day, we wanted to be so close
that we couldn't even breathe.

192
00:12:48,040 --> 00:12:50,560
But the other, we didn't even
want to see each other's faces.

193
00:12:50,640 --> 00:12:52,160
What finally happened, you know?

194
00:12:52,560 --> 00:12:55,580
We still ended up eating
at the same dining table anyway.

195
00:12:58,200 --> 00:13:00,320
Don't let the problem
last overnight.

196
00:13:00,620 --> 00:13:01,820
Letting it last overnight

197
00:13:01,840 --> 00:13:03,960
can turn a small issue
into something bigger.

198
00:13:05,000 --> 00:13:06,200
Yes, Grandpa.

199
00:13:08,200 --> 00:13:10,300
Even though it starts with a fight,

200
00:13:10,320 --> 00:13:12,500
it must end with reconciliation.

201
00:13:13,360 --> 00:13:14,720
With your lover,

202
00:13:15,160 --> 00:13:17,000
it's better to compromise.

203
00:13:17,440 --> 00:13:19,920
Therefore, go settle it properly,

204
00:13:20,780 --> 00:13:23,200
and get back together.

205
00:13:23,480 --> 00:13:24,360
Yes, Grandpa.

206
00:13:41,280 --> 00:13:43,280
Do Grandpa and Grandma
know everything, too?

207
00:13:44,920 --> 00:13:45,840
Grandma does,

208
00:13:46,600 --> 00:13:47,640
but Grandpa doesn't.

209
00:13:48,600 --> 00:13:50,360
What about the three feng shui masters,

210
00:13:51,440 --> 00:13:52,520
their prophecies,

211
00:13:53,100 --> 00:13:54,100
and the wedding?

212
00:13:55,360 --> 00:13:56,840
Those were also your plans, right?

213
00:13:57,560 --> 00:13:59,000
Grandma and I planned them

214
00:14:00,200 --> 00:14:02,040
because we wanted you to stay with us.

215
00:14:06,320 --> 00:14:07,160
Thanks a lot.

216
00:14:09,160 --> 00:14:10,120
Overall...

217
00:14:10,520 --> 00:14:11,680
In the past,

218
00:14:12,140 --> 00:14:13,700
there wasn't anything real at all, right?

219
00:14:16,040 --> 00:14:18,200
You probably just wanted
to make love with me

220
00:14:19,200 --> 00:14:21,440
and treated me as someone
to satisfy your sexual desire, didn't you?

221
00:14:22,320 --> 00:14:23,360
It wasn't like that.

222
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:27,240
I've started these lies,

223
00:14:29,040 --> 00:14:31,760
so getting out of your life
and everyone else's here

224
00:14:33,160 --> 00:14:34,760
might be the best apology I could give.

225
00:16:11,360 --> 00:16:14,360
I'm not going to judge
who is right or wrong.

226
00:16:15,640 --> 00:16:17,120
But I just want to let you know this.

227
00:16:22,040 --> 00:16:23,440
"With lies,

228
00:16:24,680 --> 00:16:26,560
your relationship can never go further."

229
00:16:28,880 --> 00:16:31,280
The foundation of love is sincerity,

230
00:16:31,700 --> 00:16:33,320
not lies.

231
00:16:34,560 --> 00:16:37,100
Lies might help us avoid the problems

232
00:16:37,120 --> 00:16:39,760
today, tomorrow,
or even the day after tomorrow,

233
00:16:40,180 --> 00:16:43,280
but they can't help us every day.

234
00:16:43,920 --> 00:16:45,040
Right, Grandma?

235
00:16:56,320 --> 00:16:58,140
"Telling a lot of lies to others

236
00:16:58,160 --> 00:17:00,680
will make you lie to yourself at the end."

237
00:17:02,040 --> 00:17:03,400
Is there anything you want to tell me?

238
00:17:04,599 --> 00:17:05,359
You, too.

239
00:17:05,740 --> 00:17:06,480
Itthi.

240
00:17:06,819 --> 00:17:09,400
Are you two keeping something from me?

241
00:17:11,800 --> 00:17:14,060
We're family, you know?

242
00:17:14,079 --> 00:17:16,530
Isn't it better to tell the truth
to each other?

243
00:17:17,619 --> 00:17:19,480
I'm this old.

244
00:17:21,460 --> 00:17:24,540
I don't want your secrets

245
00:17:24,560 --> 00:17:26,800
to be harder than my sickness.

246
00:17:33,060 --> 00:17:34,540
What did you know?

247
00:17:34,560 --> 00:17:36,000
Did anyone tell you something?

248
00:17:38,600 --> 00:17:40,700
No one had to tell me anything.

249
00:17:40,720 --> 00:17:43,840
I saw it with my own eyes.

250
00:17:44,720 --> 00:17:47,540
I saw your worried eyes
every time you looked at me,

251
00:17:47,560 --> 00:17:50,840
as if I'm about to disappear soon or something.

252
00:17:50,900 --> 00:17:53,060
The changes among people
living in the same house

253
00:17:53,080 --> 00:17:55,020
can be sensed through their eyes.

254
00:17:55,040 --> 00:17:56,480
Did you think I couldn't figure it out?

255
00:17:56,680 --> 00:17:58,120
You, too, Itthi.

256
00:17:58,860 --> 00:18:01,850
At this age, haven't you known me yet?

257
00:18:04,120 --> 00:18:07,360
Life is like brewing tea.

258
00:18:07,560 --> 00:18:09,720
Whether it's sweet or bitter,

259
00:18:10,720 --> 00:18:14,280
it depends on the drinkers' minds
by the time they drink it.

260
00:18:18,520 --> 00:18:20,480
I'm not afraid of death at all,

261
00:18:21,860 --> 00:18:23,560
but I'm afraid

262
00:18:25,420 --> 00:18:29,280
I won't get to spend enough time
laughing with you two

263
00:18:30,040 --> 00:18:31,760
before passing away.

264
00:18:50,760 --> 00:18:53,060
So, from now on,

265
00:18:53,080 --> 00:18:54,360
don't lie to me anymore.

266
00:18:55,240 --> 00:18:57,420
Don't say it's good if it's actually not.

267
00:18:57,440 --> 00:19:00,280
If you want to cry, just cry.
Tell me whatever you want to tell.

268
00:19:00,500 --> 00:19:02,260
Life is shorter than you think.

269
00:19:04,400 --> 00:19:07,080
Don't waste your time
on acting to each other.

270
00:19:07,580 --> 00:19:09,200
Be honest with one another.

271
00:19:12,120 --> 00:19:14,480
Don't lie to people
in the same house, okay?

272
00:19:20,080 --> 00:19:21,600
I'm sorry.

273
00:19:23,300 --> 00:19:25,300
I don't want you to worry.

274
00:19:26,460 --> 00:19:27,840
Seeing you sick

275
00:19:28,300 --> 00:19:30,320
makes us feel sick, too.

276
00:19:32,540 --> 00:19:33,640
So I just thought that

277
00:19:34,320 --> 00:19:36,560
keeping this from you

278
00:19:38,280 --> 00:19:41,720
could make you happy for a few more days.

279
00:19:44,540 --> 00:19:46,880
We wanted your remaining days

280
00:19:47,520 --> 00:19:50,280
to be as happy as possible.

281
00:19:51,560 --> 00:19:53,460
I'm not going to die soon.

282
00:19:53,480 --> 00:19:55,760
Cancer just comes to warn me.

283
00:19:55,780 --> 00:19:57,020
To make me realize

284
00:19:57,040 --> 00:19:59,680
that I should take care of my health more.

285
00:20:01,440 --> 00:20:02,440
You, too, Itthi.

286
00:20:02,760 --> 00:20:05,680
Don't bring those three fake
feng shui masters here again.

287
00:20:05,960 --> 00:20:07,440
They weren't good at acting at all.

288
00:20:07,680 --> 00:20:08,680
You know that?

289
00:20:08,720 --> 00:20:10,520
Of course, I do!

290
00:20:13,790 --> 00:20:15,840
Belief and faith

291
00:20:16,280 --> 00:20:18,480
are sometimes like a walking stick

292
00:20:19,040 --> 00:20:20,600
that supports our spirit,

293
00:20:20,960 --> 00:20:23,200
so I used those three feng shui masters

294
00:20:23,880 --> 00:20:26,360
as our moral support.

295
00:20:27,360 --> 00:20:29,520
Good prophecies

296
00:20:30,600 --> 00:20:32,600
are sometimes healthy
for our minds, aren't they?

297
00:20:34,880 --> 00:20:35,880
Thank you so much.

298
00:20:36,800 --> 00:20:38,800
Thank you so much, Itthi.

299
00:20:40,280 --> 00:20:41,520
But from now on,

300
00:20:42,540 --> 00:20:43,880
you have to tell me only the truth, okay?

301
00:20:45,080 --> 00:20:46,200
No more lies.

302
00:20:46,540 --> 00:20:47,160
Yeah.

303
00:20:49,640 --> 00:20:50,680
Also, Itthi,

304
00:20:52,860 --> 00:20:54,920
go settle it properly with Ritt.

305
00:20:56,080 --> 00:20:58,320
No matter what, bring him back.

306
00:20:59,760 --> 00:21:02,320
There is only one trick
I'm going to share with you.

307
00:21:03,340 --> 00:21:05,160
Persistence is key.

308
00:21:05,600 --> 00:21:06,600
Right?

309
00:21:06,800 --> 00:21:08,640
I've always been using this trick.

310
00:21:08,760 --> 00:21:09,800
Your grandma

311
00:21:10,120 --> 00:21:13,920
surrendered to me
because of my persistence, you know?

312
00:21:15,720 --> 00:21:16,560
Got it, Grandpa.

313
00:21:17,800 --> 00:21:18,960
Come on, let me have a hug.

314
00:21:44,420 --> 00:21:45,780
You should get into a wheelchair first.

315
00:21:46,120 --> 00:21:46,820
It's okay.

316
00:21:46,840 --> 00:21:48,240
Alright, walk carefully.

317
00:21:48,920 --> 00:21:50,720
Your mother looks much stronger.

318
00:21:50,950 --> 00:21:52,400
She doesn't need a walking stick anymore.

319
00:21:53,460 --> 00:21:55,520
She has recently started doing
physical therapy on her own.

320
00:21:59,880 --> 00:22:00,720
Come on, Mom.

321
00:22:02,500 --> 00:22:04,220
Hey, do you see?

322
00:22:04,600 --> 00:22:06,880
I can walk much better on my own now.

323
00:22:07,340 --> 00:22:08,760
Very good of you, Mom.

324
00:22:08,960 --> 00:22:11,340
Soon, you'll be able to sit in the front row,

325
00:22:11,360 --> 00:22:13,280
cheering on a newbie idol in Korea soon.

326
00:22:14,000 --> 00:22:14,640
Huh?

327
00:22:16,340 --> 00:22:18,840
Did I just miss something?

328
00:22:20,320 --> 00:22:21,880
Are you going to get back to auditioning?

329
00:22:22,350 --> 00:22:24,440
Since when? Why didn't you tell me that?

330
00:22:25,200 --> 00:22:26,060
Well...

331
00:22:26,580 --> 00:22:28,240
I'm not sure yet.

332
00:22:29,240 --> 00:22:30,380
I just think that

333
00:22:30,410 --> 00:22:32,640
there are a lot of things I want to do now

334
00:22:33,140 --> 00:22:34,320
before flying back.

335
00:22:36,480 --> 00:22:38,120
The opportunity you've got

336
00:22:38,540 --> 00:22:40,760
is what many people want to have.

337
00:22:42,160 --> 00:22:44,240
Don't let it go.

338
00:22:47,980 --> 00:22:48,840
I know.

339
00:22:49,320 --> 00:22:51,520
But sometimes, where we really want to be

340
00:22:51,700 --> 00:22:54,560
matters more than the opportunities we have.

341
00:22:56,560 --> 00:22:59,100
So, where do you really want to be?

342
00:23:04,600 --> 00:23:06,720
If I guess, that probably is...

343
00:23:07,160 --> 00:23:09,560
making other people happy,

344
00:23:10,680 --> 00:23:14,160
like when he taught
the younger ones dance.

345
00:23:19,940 --> 00:23:20,920
Sometimes,

346
00:23:21,260 --> 00:23:24,840
I just want to be somewhere
that can bring peace to my mind.

347
00:23:29,580 --> 00:23:30,960
I understand

348
00:23:32,440 --> 00:23:34,960
that your whole life might have felt restricted,

349
00:23:37,400 --> 00:23:38,520
whether because of me,

350
00:23:39,020 --> 00:23:40,520
or the agency there.

351
00:23:44,220 --> 00:23:46,220
But I also want to see you
live with happiness.

352
00:23:48,640 --> 00:23:49,840
And happiness

353
00:23:50,920 --> 00:23:52,440
will come to you

354
00:23:53,040 --> 00:23:54,560
when you are brave enough to choose

355
00:23:55,070 --> 00:23:56,520
and brave enough to lose.

356
00:24:00,560 --> 00:24:02,440
No matter which way you choose,

357
00:24:05,380 --> 00:24:07,280
I'll always be here

358
00:24:08,660 --> 00:24:10,660
to see your success.

359
00:24:18,560 --> 00:24:19,580
Me, too.

360
00:24:26,600 --> 00:24:27,760
Thank you, Mom.

361
00:24:37,680 --> 00:24:40,060
So, this can be the order

362
00:24:40,080 --> 00:24:42,320
for the presentation.

363
00:24:43,080 --> 00:24:44,680
Does anyone have any questions

364
00:24:45,280 --> 00:24:46,800
about the final presentation?

365
00:24:47,080 --> 00:24:49,240
Is there a second chance
in case we don't pass?

366
00:24:50,880 --> 00:24:53,880
Don't get used to
getting a second or third chance.

367
00:24:54,600 --> 00:24:56,600
For some things,
if you miss your chance, that's it.

368
00:24:57,540 --> 00:24:58,520
So,

369
00:24:58,840 --> 00:25:01,680
don't expect a second chance.

370
00:25:02,320 --> 00:25:03,640
Some opportunities

371
00:25:03,920 --> 00:25:06,120
only present themselves once.

372
00:25:07,480 --> 00:25:08,840
Got it, professor.

373
00:25:10,160 --> 00:25:10,960
Well,

374
00:25:11,440 --> 00:25:13,120
if you don't have any questions,

375
00:25:13,360 --> 00:25:15,080
see you on the presentation day.

376
00:25:15,880 --> 00:25:16,920
I'm rooting for you all.

377
00:25:37,980 --> 00:25:38,960
Is there anything

378
00:25:39,120 --> 00:25:40,440
that I should know?

379
00:25:40,900 --> 00:25:42,440
What else haven't you told me yet?

380
00:25:58,960 --> 00:26:00,480
- Be careful, Mom.
- Okay.

381
00:26:12,000 --> 00:26:13,320
Thank you so much.

382
00:26:14,340 --> 00:26:15,760
I think I'm going to go to my room.

383
00:26:15,800 --> 00:26:17,080
I just want to take some rest.

384
00:26:19,120 --> 00:26:21,600
And you, check the fridge to see
if there's anything to eat.

385
00:26:21,780 --> 00:26:23,360
Warm it up for Pure, too, okay?

386
00:26:24,140 --> 00:26:24,940
Yes, Mom.

387
00:26:26,800 --> 00:26:29,200
You can sit down
and catch your breath first, Pure.

388
00:26:29,680 --> 00:26:31,360
You gave me a ride all morning.

389
00:26:31,460 --> 00:26:32,480
Yes, Mom.

390
00:26:33,620 --> 00:26:34,600
Take care of your friend.

391
00:26:34,740 --> 00:26:35,560
Yes, Mom.

392
00:26:48,640 --> 00:26:50,120
Thank you so much for taking us home.

393
00:26:51,160 --> 00:26:52,280
No problem.

394
00:26:52,960 --> 00:26:54,340
I feel like your mom is my mom,

395
00:26:55,260 --> 00:26:56,680
the same way that you and I

396
00:26:56,900 --> 00:26:58,080
are like the same person.

397
00:26:59,720 --> 00:27:00,680
By saying this,

398
00:27:01,060 --> 00:27:02,520
do you want to go back to Korea with me?

399
00:27:03,440 --> 00:27:04,720
Let me be one of your fans

400
00:27:05,120 --> 00:27:06,600
who waits for you here.

401
00:27:07,320 --> 00:27:09,160
When you have a concert in Thailand,

402
00:27:09,260 --> 00:27:12,180
I'll immediately book a front-row ticket.

403
00:27:15,900 --> 00:27:16,640
Okay.

404
00:27:16,940 --> 00:27:18,600
Are you hungry?
What do you want to have?

405
00:27:20,200 --> 00:27:21,760
What can I have?

406
00:27:23,140 --> 00:27:24,360
So, what do you want?

407
00:27:25,640 --> 00:27:28,300
Mmm... Can I have this one?

408
00:27:28,320 --> 00:27:30,720
Hey, what are you doing?
What if Mom sees it?

409
00:27:31,480 --> 00:27:33,160
I just want to have you.

410
00:27:33,340 --> 00:27:34,400
I'm hungry.

411
00:27:35,000 --> 00:27:37,000
Let me enjoy you now

412
00:27:37,260 --> 00:27:40,640
before you become famous without me there.

413
00:27:41,600 --> 00:27:42,360
Whoa.

414
00:27:42,740 --> 00:27:44,200
Is this the only thing on your mind, huh?

415
00:27:44,580 --> 00:27:46,940
It isn't like that. Don't get me wrong.

416
00:27:46,960 --> 00:27:48,360
You just said it.

417
00:27:49,320 --> 00:27:51,680
I can't deny

418
00:27:52,740 --> 00:27:54,560
that I've been obsessed
with you since that night.

419
00:27:54,740 --> 00:27:55,520
There you go.

420
00:27:55,700 --> 00:27:56,360
But...

421
00:27:56,720 --> 00:27:57,880
Listen to me first.

422
00:27:58,160 --> 00:27:59,360
That isn't all.

423
00:28:07,360 --> 00:28:08,880
The more I look at you...

424
00:28:10,680 --> 00:28:11,800
the more I want to know you.

425
00:28:14,440 --> 00:28:15,720
The closer I get to you,

426
00:28:18,000 --> 00:28:20,080
the deeper I want to go.

427
00:28:22,880 --> 00:28:23,800
How deep?

428
00:28:25,600 --> 00:28:27,020
Deep enough to reach your dream

429
00:28:28,800 --> 00:28:30,360
you've never told anyone about.

430
00:28:33,020 --> 00:28:34,400
Deep enough to your fear

431
00:28:36,680 --> 00:28:38,080
that has been kept inside you.

432
00:28:41,840 --> 00:28:43,760
Deep enough to reach your true self,

433
00:28:45,560 --> 00:28:47,180
the one you're afraid to show anyone,

434
00:28:48,040 --> 00:28:49,240
even your mother.

435
00:28:52,300 --> 00:28:53,900
I want to know Pitcha,

436
00:28:55,700 --> 00:28:56,840
who doesn't have to be great,

437
00:28:59,420 --> 00:29:00,460
be forced,

438
00:29:02,320 --> 00:29:03,800
or do anything for others.

439
00:29:06,840 --> 00:29:07,780
The one...

440
00:29:09,520 --> 00:29:11,120
who can't hide anything from me.

441
00:29:15,520 --> 00:29:16,900
I also mean that thing.

442
00:29:18,160 --> 00:29:19,040
You're mischievous.

443
00:29:19,920 --> 00:29:21,880
I really want to get to know you better.

444
00:29:27,300 --> 00:29:28,540
Really?

445
00:29:30,100 --> 00:29:31,020
It's true.

446
00:29:38,700 --> 00:29:39,620
If so...

447
00:29:40,400 --> 00:29:41,760
I'll let you know me

448
00:29:43,240 --> 00:29:44,760
deeper than you ever have before.

449
00:33:48,320 --> 00:33:49,320
Are you okay?

450
00:33:50,800 --> 00:33:51,840
Okay with what?

451
00:33:52,100 --> 00:33:52,880
With...

452
00:33:59,780 --> 00:34:01,200
So you're going to leave
after you're finished?

453
00:34:01,480 --> 00:34:02,440
Of course.

454
00:34:02,800 --> 00:34:04,720
What do you want me to do
after finishing, huh?

455
00:34:08,520 --> 00:34:09,560
I'm kidding.

456
00:34:11,400 --> 00:34:12,679
Making a sulky face, huh?

457
00:34:14,179 --> 00:34:14,960
Gotcha.

458
00:34:15,239 --> 00:34:17,199
Do you have a sensitive side as well?

459
00:34:19,080 --> 00:34:20,239
You're so mischievous,

460
00:34:20,920 --> 00:34:22,000
always teasing me.

461
00:34:22,320 --> 00:34:23,719
It's because you're so easy to tease.

462
00:34:33,120 --> 00:34:35,880
My feelings for you aren't
just when we're in bed.

463
00:34:37,380 --> 00:34:38,719
If that were the case,

464
00:34:39,920 --> 00:34:41,920
I might not feel this way...

465
00:34:42,600 --> 00:34:43,639
every time I see your face.

466
00:34:47,560 --> 00:34:48,520
What do you mean by

467
00:34:49,480 --> 00:34:50,440
"this way"?

468
00:34:52,199 --> 00:34:53,159
I mean

469
00:34:54,860 --> 00:34:58,320
I'm afraid that one day, you'll be so famous
that you won't remember me.

470
00:34:59,640 --> 00:35:01,520
But I'm willing to let you forget me

471
00:35:02,880 --> 00:35:04,480
if that's the way you've chosen.

472
00:35:10,560 --> 00:35:12,760
Don't you want to hold me back,
so I can stay with the girls,

473
00:35:15,500 --> 00:35:16,680
or even with you?

474
00:35:19,800 --> 00:35:22,080
I know you have your own path

475
00:35:23,360 --> 00:35:24,920
to reach your dream.

476
00:35:30,060 --> 00:35:31,400
I'm not going to hold you back.

477
00:35:32,260 --> 00:35:33,720
I don't even want to do that,

478
00:35:35,800 --> 00:35:37,800
but there is one thing I want you to know.

479
00:35:39,600 --> 00:35:41,680
I genuinely have
a good feeling about you.

480
00:35:43,800 --> 00:35:47,040
As genuinely as anyone could possibly feel.

481
00:35:51,720 --> 00:35:52,760
Thank you for that.

482
00:35:55,280 --> 00:35:56,520
I also hope that

483
00:35:57,000 --> 00:35:59,760
no matter how far apart we are,

484
00:36:01,280 --> 00:36:03,880
there will still be a day
when you miss me.

485
00:36:05,400 --> 00:36:07,400
Just a little bit is fine.

486
00:36:18,440 --> 00:36:20,000
Whether I live in Korea

487
00:36:20,720 --> 00:36:21,800
or anywhere else,

488
00:36:23,200 --> 00:36:25,040
I'll never forget that, once,

489
00:36:26,160 --> 00:36:28,640
we were
in each other's arms like this.

490
00:36:29,760 --> 00:36:32,280
I'm truly glad we got to know each other.

491
00:36:58,500 --> 00:36:59,720
Are you leaving?

492
00:37:02,360 --> 00:37:04,760
I think I'm going to check

493
00:37:04,980 --> 00:37:06,000
how Ritt is doing for a bit.

494
00:37:08,460 --> 00:37:09,160
Mmm.

495
00:37:10,120 --> 00:37:11,880
I'm not sure who
I should feel more sorry for.

496
00:37:12,220 --> 00:37:13,640
They did it to themselves.

497
00:37:14,040 --> 00:37:15,720
Fooling each other as if they were kids.

498
00:37:18,520 --> 00:37:20,360
You can feel sorry for me first.

499
00:37:22,000 --> 00:37:23,000
Sorry for what?

500
00:37:24,260 --> 00:37:28,360
For my short time of happiness with you.

501
00:37:29,040 --> 00:37:30,480
In just a little while...

502
00:37:30,800 --> 00:37:32,720
you'll leave me far behind.

503
00:37:34,480 --> 00:37:35,200
What?

504
00:37:35,600 --> 00:37:38,440
What kind of person are you
to make others feel guilty with your words?

505
00:37:51,920 --> 00:37:53,160
Before you go,

506
00:37:55,280 --> 00:37:56,800
can we do it every day?

507
00:37:57,860 --> 00:37:58,860
Jeez!

508
00:38:01,360 --> 00:38:03,040
I really mean it.

509
00:38:03,420 --> 00:38:04,200
Please.

510
00:38:04,480 --> 00:38:06,260
- Please, please.
- No, stop it.

511
00:38:06,280 --> 00:38:08,280
- Please, please.
- Hey...

512
00:38:09,260 --> 00:38:10,700
Let's do it again.

513
00:38:10,720 --> 00:38:12,460
Hey, that's enough.

514
00:38:12,480 --> 00:38:13,480
One more time, please.

515
00:38:14,240 --> 00:38:15,360
Hey, you!

516
00:38:15,800 --> 00:38:17,480
That's enough. You're going to wake my mom up.

517
00:38:17,500 --> 00:38:18,720
You, stop. Stop it.

518
00:38:22,640 --> 00:38:23,480
Okay, fine.

519
00:38:39,800 --> 00:38:41,800
Here. In case you get hungry.

520
00:38:46,360 --> 00:38:47,400
Thanks.

521
00:39:13,820 --> 00:39:14,920
How are you, though?

522
00:39:19,200 --> 00:39:20,360
What am I supposed to say?

523
00:39:26,800 --> 00:39:27,980
Actually,

524
00:39:28,240 --> 00:39:31,560
I've always been trying
to make you tell Itthi the truth,

525
00:39:32,040 --> 00:39:33,560
- but you still...
- I know!

526
00:39:34,640 --> 00:39:36,240
I know it was my fault.

527
00:39:36,740 --> 00:39:38,600
Are you here just to pile on me?

528
00:39:43,860 --> 00:39:45,160
And for Pitcha,

529
00:39:45,480 --> 00:39:47,480
he also didn't want to
help Itthi trick you,

530
00:39:47,680 --> 00:39:49,690
- but he just...
- You...

531
00:39:49,710 --> 00:39:52,160
knew that Pitcha knew about this?

532
00:39:54,220 --> 00:39:55,460
You knew all of this

533
00:39:56,800 --> 00:39:58,320
was part of the plan of...

534
00:40:05,840 --> 00:40:07,040
When did you know it?

535
00:40:12,020 --> 00:40:14,560
Your friend, Master Ritt,
should take some acting classes,

536
00:40:15,320 --> 00:40:16,800
or screenwriting courses.

537
00:40:17,200 --> 00:40:18,160
Why did you say that?

538
00:40:18,340 --> 00:40:20,040
Because he's impersonating me

539
00:40:20,920 --> 00:40:23,040
and lying to Itthi that
he's his sweetheart.

540
00:40:23,340 --> 00:40:24,840
Who told you this?

541
00:40:26,480 --> 00:40:27,520
Well...

542
00:40:29,200 --> 00:40:30,320
You have to help me out.

543
00:40:31,240 --> 00:40:32,520
I really like this person.

544
00:40:33,280 --> 00:40:34,680
But tricking him like this...

545
00:40:35,320 --> 00:40:36,440
How is this going to work out?

546
00:40:36,800 --> 00:40:38,080
He tricked me first,

547
00:40:38,460 --> 00:40:40,400
so I just tricked him back. It's fair.

548
00:40:41,060 --> 00:40:42,120
Fine,

549
00:40:42,640 --> 00:40:43,560
I'll help you.

550
00:40:43,720 --> 00:40:44,920
But where is it again?

551
00:40:45,240 --> 00:40:46,840
I'll send you the bar's location.

552
00:40:47,240 --> 00:40:49,000
What's the name of the bar?

553
00:40:49,040 --> 00:40:50,000
Magic Move.

554
00:40:51,000 --> 00:40:53,360
It's a new bar near my campus.

555
00:40:53,880 --> 00:40:54,640
Okay.

556
00:40:55,160 --> 00:40:56,160
Please handle it for me.

557
00:40:56,460 --> 00:40:57,680
You really like him, huh?

558
00:40:59,880 --> 00:41:00,960
Actually,

559
00:41:01,440 --> 00:41:03,600
Itthi asked me to see Master Ritt for a reading.

560
00:41:10,620 --> 00:41:12,620
You've known about it for so long,
but you didn't tell me.

561
00:41:14,220 --> 00:41:16,200
You let me become a clown
in everyone's eyes.

562
00:41:18,000 --> 00:41:20,520
I just wanted to know
what you would do next.

563
00:41:20,820 --> 00:41:22,700
- Also, Pitcha...
- Stop it.

564
00:41:25,500 --> 00:41:26,600
Do you know...

565
00:41:29,220 --> 00:41:30,760
that you're my best friend, Pure?

566
00:41:33,240 --> 00:41:34,560
And I love you so much.

567
00:41:36,720 --> 00:41:39,400
But look what you did to me.

568
00:41:40,320 --> 00:41:41,800
It isn't what you think at all.

569
00:41:43,240 --> 00:41:45,680
- I just...
- I'm really hurt...

570
00:41:49,320 --> 00:41:50,600
that he tricked me.

571
00:41:52,760 --> 00:41:54,200
But my best friend

572
00:41:55,640 --> 00:41:57,160
was even in on it as well.

573
00:42:00,680 --> 00:42:03,240
Who can I still trust in this world?

574
00:42:07,100 --> 00:42:08,120
Hey, Ritt.

575
00:42:11,600 --> 00:42:13,400
Thanks for coming.

576
00:42:14,880 --> 00:42:16,080
I'm so impressed.

577
00:42:18,780 --> 00:42:19,780
I used to think

578
00:42:21,120 --> 00:42:22,200
that at least

579
00:42:23,800 --> 00:42:26,480
I had a friend
who'd always be by my side.

580
00:42:31,820 --> 00:42:33,080
But now I realize

581
00:42:34,760 --> 00:42:35,840
that I...

582
00:42:38,000 --> 00:42:39,840
don't have anyone sincere left anymore.

583
00:42:45,240 --> 00:42:47,080
I can't feel any worse than this.

584
00:42:50,280 --> 00:42:51,440
Just get out of my room.

585
00:43:19,640 --> 00:43:22,200
[Ansuz: communication and revelation]

586
00:43:26,700 --> 00:43:28,480
Guess it's time for the truth

587
00:43:29,920 --> 00:43:31,680
to speak for itself instead of prophecies.

588
00:43:55,280 --> 00:43:56,160
Look over there.

589
00:43:56,400 --> 00:43:58,200
Thank you so much.

590
00:43:58,720 --> 00:44:00,380
Hey!

591
00:44:00,400 --> 00:44:01,720
What?!

592
00:44:01,840 --> 00:44:03,820
- What?!
- They're just snacks.

593
00:44:03,840 --> 00:44:05,140
Enough with the "Hey, hey, hey."

594
00:44:05,160 --> 00:44:06,120
I'm shipping this.

595
00:44:06,150 --> 00:44:08,220
- Are you two a thing?
- I just bought him some snacks.

596
00:44:08,240 --> 00:44:10,320
So sweet of you!

597
00:44:34,280 --> 00:44:36,360
- Here is your drink.
- Thanks.

598
00:45:20,580 --> 00:45:22,680
No matter how hard I try,

599
00:45:25,900 --> 00:45:28,760
nothing will ever change.

600
00:45:32,000 --> 00:45:33,040
But now...

601
00:45:35,980 --> 00:45:37,280
it hurts a lot more.

602
00:47:12,880 --> 00:47:13,960
Their prophecies

603
00:47:14,560 --> 00:47:15,520
and the wedding?

604
00:47:16,880 --> 00:47:18,360
Those were also your plans, right?

605
00:47:26,280 --> 00:47:27,520
Liars like us,

606
00:47:28,480 --> 00:47:30,480
who love to make up stories,

607
00:47:31,020 --> 00:47:32,360
aren't supposed to be together.

608
00:47:34,160 --> 00:47:35,800
It's not going to work anyway.

609
00:47:47,040 --> 00:47:48,240
Can you please come back?

610
00:49:28,560 --> 00:49:29,080
Ritt.

611
00:49:29,360 --> 00:49:30,640
I still want to explain.

612
00:49:32,000 --> 00:49:33,720
I didn't mean for it to turn out that way.

613
00:49:35,040 --> 00:49:36,400
It started when you...

614
00:49:36,780 --> 00:49:38,240
Whether you meant it or not,

615
00:49:38,500 --> 00:49:39,880
it doesn't matter anymore.

616
00:49:42,060 --> 00:49:42,880
That's enough, Itthi.

617
00:49:44,300 --> 00:49:45,680
Let it end this way.

618
00:49:50,100 --> 00:49:52,900
I still believe that
the sincerity between us

619
00:49:52,920 --> 00:49:54,520
can fix this.

620
00:49:56,000 --> 00:49:57,320
- Let's begin...
- Listen.

621
00:49:58,880 --> 00:50:00,360
I've indeed used those stones

622
00:50:00,560 --> 00:50:01,680
to deceive you

623
00:50:02,440 --> 00:50:03,680
and others.

624
00:50:05,120 --> 00:50:06,040
But do you know

625
00:50:07,150 --> 00:50:09,800
what's more deceptive than my prophecies?

626
00:50:11,620 --> 00:50:13,520
It's your words that sounded heartfelt.

627
00:50:17,720 --> 00:50:19,880
I don't think we can fix it anymore.

628
00:50:21,940 --> 00:50:23,940
The only thing we can do

629
00:50:24,880 --> 00:50:26,280
is not let those lies

630
00:50:27,840 --> 00:50:30,280
and fake feelings escalate any further.

631
00:50:32,520 --> 00:50:33,560
Let's accept that,

632
00:50:34,550 --> 00:50:35,640
up until now,

633
00:50:38,000 --> 00:50:39,940
our love was never real to begin with.

634
00:50:57,440 --> 00:50:58,360
I'll take it.

635
00:51:01,960 --> 00:51:03,720
And let's end it here.

636
00:51:50,400 --> 00:51:52,040
Fooling each other...

637
00:51:52,140 --> 00:51:53,080
In the end,

638
00:51:53,560 --> 00:51:54,920
you can't avoid the truth anyway.

639
00:51:56,540 --> 00:51:57,960
If he did what you did,

640
00:51:58,420 --> 00:51:59,640
it's fair game, isn't it?

641
00:51:59,700 --> 00:52:00,720
If you rob a thief,

642
00:52:01,600 --> 00:52:03,080
you become a thief.

643
00:52:04,880 --> 00:52:07,000
Fate brought two people together.

644
00:52:10,240 --> 00:52:12,080
Coincidences don't usually happen.

645
00:52:12,480 --> 00:52:14,400
If you want to keep him safe,

646
00:52:14,840 --> 00:52:15,960
give me one million baht.

647
00:52:18,080 --> 00:52:19,040
Where is Ritt?

648
00:52:29,400 --> 00:52:33,200
♫Is it pure coincidence?♫

649
00:52:33,450 --> 00:52:37,520
♫Or is it destiny that decides?♫

650
00:52:37,550 --> 00:52:39,860
♫Is someone above drawing all these lines?♫

651
00:52:39,880 --> 00:52:45,400
♫Or playing matchmaker in disguise?♫

652
00:52:46,020 --> 00:52:50,220
♫What if the stars shift in their place♫

653
00:52:50,460 --> 00:52:54,000
♫Slightly out of line,♫

654
00:52:54,650 --> 00:52:58,340
♫Will our orbits still align?♫

655
00:52:58,370 --> 00:53:02,680
♫Try answering if your world
will cross with mine♫

656
00:53:02,710 --> 00:53:06,760
♫Though the destiny between us
is differently defined♫

657
00:53:06,790 --> 00:53:12,090
♫I believe our love will change our♫

658
00:53:12,400 --> 00:53:16,250
♫Destiny, rewrite prophecies♫

659
00:53:16,300 --> 00:53:20,350
♫Even if they are against our destiny♫

660
00:53:20,380 --> 00:53:22,780
♫(But we're gonna try, try, try)♫

661
00:53:22,800 --> 00:53:28,220
♫And I believe our love has power♫

662
00:53:28,240 --> 00:53:32,240
♫I believe the love of us♫

663
00:53:32,500 --> 00:53:40,570
♫Will realign the stars back to the line
where they should be♫

664
00:53:40,600 --> 00:53:43,840
♫(And we're gonna try, try, try)♫
